contents.value: Communicate with Ex about Unacceptable Behavior
FOB talk to the Mom of his children
SM practiced with AB sitting up
AB was crying while lying on his belly. SM sat AB up and AB was content.
SM sat behind AB when AB sat on the floor and AB had her hands close to AB to help support him.
While AB was playing with his feet SM said with a laugh to AB "are you gonna get your toes!"

SM stated she has been helping AB learn how to sit up by placing him in the floor more and also when AB is in his activity center she no longer uses a blanket around his chest to support him so that it forces AB to support himself.
SM showed AB how to push/roll the toy truck back and forth and AB grabbed the truck and played with the toy truck.

SM stated she is very stressed and frustrated with the mother of FOB's children. The woman has been contacting FOB and trying to cause problems. FOB has asked the woman to stop but she continues with the inappropriate behavior. SM is trying to avoid coming in contact with the woman but SM is strongly encouraging FOB to do something about the situation.

The visit took place in the home of SM.
SM was feeding AB a bottle when OS first arrived. SM was all ready for work and had AB's things together for the babysitter. SM is very appreciative of her baby sitter and says AB seems to enjoy it. 
SM talked to OS about the family Christmas tree that they had decorated and SM allowed each of the children to by simple ornaments for the tree. The children also had Christmas stockings hung on the wall behind the tree. SM said they weren't able to put up the bigger tree this year because of the limited space but OS and SM talked about some traditions and how making memories is important.
After allowing AB to playing the floor for a while SM placed AB in the car seat and secured him and then SM followed OS outside as SM had to leave for work.

This represented most of the visit.
OS-CS
